# Bitstream-Studio rules

## Repository layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| **`extension/`** | VS Code extension + webview (Sensor Telemetry, Sensor Studio, BS2 bridge) |
| **`AGENT_HANDOFF.md`** | Session onboarding |
| **`.cursor/rules/`** | Agent policy (this folder) |

**Not in this repo:** `T3D/`, `bitstream-simulator/` (separate extension repo).

## Development

- Work in **`extension/`**: `npm install`, `npm run dev:webview`, `npm run compile`.
- Dev URLs: `http://localhost:5173/?app=bitstream`, `?app=sensor-studio`.
- Full runbook: **`extension/HOW_TO_RUN.md`**.

## No `@ternion/t3d`

Decoupling complete (2026-05-30). Webview uses local **`ui/catalog/`**, **`extension-bridge/`**, and vendored CSS — **no** npm dependency on `@ternion/t3d` or `T3D/` tree.

## VSIX

- Extension id: **`bitstream-studio`**.
- Use **`isVsCodeExtensionWebview()`** / `window.__VSCODE_API__` — not `T3DVSCodeUtils.isVsCodeMode()` alone.
- Re-test after **`npm run package`** in a clean VS Code window.

## Related

- **`bitstream-dual-runtime.mdc`** — UART + Simulator parity.
- **`tesaiot-firmware-bitstream-paths.mdc`** — firmware truth paths.
